Russian Equity Movers: Aeroflot, Polymetal, Uralkali Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-27T15:50:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/russian-equity-movers-aeroflot-polymetal-uralkali-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rallied
2.5 percent to 1,380.42 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, paring
an earlier gain of as much as 3.3 percent. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index added 4.2 percent to 1,369.93.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX) extended gains after Deputy Chief
Executive Officer Shamil Kurmashov said Russiaâ€™s largest airline
may buy back shares after prices declined. The stock advanced
3.6 percent to 50.82 rubles, the biggest increase since Sept. 7.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), the Russian silver and gold
producer, rose for the first day in four as both metals
advanced. The shares increased as much as 6.6 percent before
closing 2.1 percent higher at 549.5 rubles.  OAO  Uralkali (URKA)   jumped for a second day after its
trader, Belarusian Potash Co., said it will increase the price
of potash for immediate delivery to  Brazil  by $30 a ton, or more
than 5 percent, in the fourth quarter. The shares rose 4.4
percent to 252.72 rubles, the biggest gain since July 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
